    "body": "```\n$ cat /etc/*-release | grep \\^NAME; python --version; cython --version    \nNAME=\"Arch Linux\"\nPython 3.5.2\nCython version 0.24.1\n```\n\nLet's create a dummy pyx in a subfolder and cythonize it:\n\n```\n$ mkdir srcdir && touch srcdir/empty.pyx && cythonize -b srcdir/empty.pyx\nCompiling /tmp/foo/srcdir/empty.pyx because it changed.\n[1/1] Cythonizing /tmp/foo/srcdir/empty.pyx\n<elided>\n```\n\nThe `.c` ends up next to the source, but the `.so` ends up somewhat unhelpfully in the current folder:\n\n```\n$ ls -R\n.:\nbuild  srcdir  empty.cpython-35m-x86_64-linux-gnu.so\n\n./build:\ntemp.linux-x86_64-3.5\n\n./build/temp.linux-x86_64-3.5:\ntmp\n\n./build/temp.linux-x86_64-3.5/tmp:\nfoo\n\n./build/temp.linux-x86_64-3.5/tmp/foo:\nsrcdir\n\n./build/temp.linux-x86_64-3.5/tmp/foo/srcdir:\nempty.o\n\n./srcdir:\nempty.c  empty.pyx\n```\n",
